{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"589cb38a-4913-4ce7-bf65-0640f723a735","content":"Here are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API or controller-based\n- Auth options: `--auth Individual` (Identity/JWT), `--auth IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `--auth SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `--auth Windows`\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` or scaffold manually\n- Auth: Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, OpenID Connect), express-session, or Auth0 SDK\n\n**Python / FastAPI**\n- `fastapi` with `python-jose` for JWT, or `authlib` for OAuth2\n\n**Java / Spring Boot**\n- Use Spring Initializr with `spring-boot-starter-security`\n- Auth: JWT, OAuth2 Resource Server, Spring Security\n\nFor a quick start with .NET:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nFor Node.js:\n```bash\nnpx express-generator MyApi\nnpm install passport passport-jwt jsonwebtoken\n```\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific one for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"59a4aede-0264-472e-a170-8d98b8ff8ee4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular options.","outputTokens":335},"id":"03765ba9-1b62-4665-944e-1f789e42c646","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:50:15.643Z","parentId":"9ef221ff-b904-4c32-9d7d-0520bccae196"}
